did.abstract: The records consist of proposals, specifications, correspondence, memoranda, reports, schedules, drawings, a 16mm film, and administrative records, maintained by the Yale Office of Facilities, documenting construction and renovation projects for Yale buildings. Also included is detailed information about the design and installation of mechanical, laboratory, and other equipment and systems.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 46-A (YRG 46-A), Records and materials broadly documenting Yale buildings, facilities, and grounds.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The records were transferred from the Office of Facilities, 1989-2008. Accession 2012-A-075 received in 2012.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Access to the records is partially restricted. See Collection Contents for details.

Original audiovisual materials, as well as preservation and duplicating masters, may not be played. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist must pay for a use copy, which is retained by the repository. Researchers wishing to obtain an additional copy for their personal use should consult Copying Services information on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Yale University Building Project Records (RU 5). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of proposals, specifications, correspondence, memoranda, reports, schedules, drawings, a 16mm film, and administrative records, maintained by the Yale Office of Facilities, documenting construction and renovation projects for Yale buildings. Also included is detailed information about the design and installation of mechanical, laboratory, and other equipment and systems.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged as follows: I. Specifications, correspondence, and other project records, 1891-1985. II. Drawings, 1912-1988; and subsequent accessions.

did.unittitle: Specifications, correspondence, and other project records

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Building specifications, cost lists, charts, reports, correspondence, memoranda, proposals, smaller drawings, and the like, from 1891 to 1985, comprise this large collection of documentation from the erstwhile Architectural and Engineering Services (now Facilities Planning). The materials address aspects of overall building construction and renovation, as well as detailed work in plumbing, ventilation, heating, air-conditioning, and electrical fixtures. The purchase, installation, and maintenance of building equipment (especially in university dining halls and science or medical laboratories) is also documented.
Please note that most drawings originally found in these files were removed for proper storage and preservation. These drawings are inventoried in Series II.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: In accordance with university policy, the records are restricted until January 1, 2021.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains architectural drawings removed from files in Series I for storage and preservation reasons.

Building construction, renovation, and maintenance plans from 1912 to 1988 comprise this set of architectural drawings, which range in content from general assignment floor plans to detailed sketches of electrical fixtures and equipment wiring. These drawings have served as important working documents to architects involved in the details of restoration, alteration, and additional building.
